Quote:  [He] has been overseas some of the time, running foreign exchange dealing rooms in Hong Kong and Los Angeles, and the term "reef fish" is new to him. I have to explain that it's a derisive term coined by David Lange to describe the behaviour of the money markets... Lange once referred to market operators as demented reef fish - a term inspired by the aberrant behaviour of tropical fish which dart backwards and forwards en masse in a manner that defies rational explanation.
